The paper proposes a new logic-based planning language and describes a planning system that implements it. The paper also discusses the system's ability to solve hard planning problems, including secure planning under incomplete initial states. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also involves logic programming, which suggests cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses benchmark problems, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
